Limitations and possibilities of applying the positive effects of human/animal relations in the treatment of psychological ailments. For the 72nd Psychiatric Saar-Lorr-Lux Symposium (Sept. 2004 at the Neuropsychiatric Hospital (CHNP) in Ettelbruck, LUXEMBOURG), Dr. Jean-Marie Spautz, director, brought together professionals of varied disciplines, each involved in Animal Assisted Therapy (AAT).